1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
3 HOUSE BILL 3065 By: Pogemiller
4
5
6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to revenue and taxation; amending 68
O.S. 2021, Section 1355, as amended by Section 1,
8 Chapter 370, O.S.L. 2023 (68 O.S. Supp. 2025, Section
1355), which relates to exemptions from sales tax and
9 subject to other tax; modifying list to include
electronic cigarettes and vapor products; defining
10 terms; creating excise tax on electronic cigarettes
and vapor products; providing excise tax be paid in
11 lieu of any other tax; requiring when excise tax be
paid; mandating retailer to file form; requiring
12 Oklahoma Tax Commission to provide forms;
establishing requirements of form; deeming tax to be
13 delinquent if not paid by certain date; charging
interest on delinquent form; requiring report to be
14 electronically filed; providing for codification; and
providing an effective date.
15
16
17
18 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
19 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 68 O.S. 2021, Section 1355, as
20 amended by Section 1, Chapter 370, O.S.L. 2023 (68 O.S. Supp. 2025,
21 Section 1355), is amended to read as follows:
22 Section 1355. Exemptions - Subject to other tax.
23 There are hereby specifically exempted from the tax levied
24 pursuant to the provisions of Section 1350 et seq. of this title:
Req. No. 14027 Page 1

1 1. Sale of gasoline, motor fuel, methanol, "M-85" which is a
2 mixture of methanol and gasoline containing at least eighty-five
3 percent (85%) methanol, compressed natural gas, liquefied natural
4 gas, or liquefied petroleum gas on which the Motor Fuel Tax,
5 Gasoline Excise Tax, Special Fuels Tax, or the fee in lieu of
6 Special Fuels Tax levied in Section 500.1 et seq., Section 601 et
7 seq. or Section 701 et seq. of this title has been, or will be paid;
8 2. For the sale of motor vehicles or any optional equipment or
9 accessories attached to motor vehicles on which the Oklahoma Motor
